Italian dairy cattle are producing
10 percent less milk because of a heat wave, even as farmers
take steps to cool the animals including showers and fans,
Coldiretti said.  Corn, tomato, beet and sunflower crops have been damaged
across the country and some areas have received no rain for
months, the Rome-based agricultural union said in an e-mailed
statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
